<A NAME=POEM1></A>
<TR ALIGN=LEFT VALIGN=TOP><TD><P><FONT SIZE=+1>glare ice
<br>
the old dog
<br>
pees on the moon
</FONT></TD></TR> <TR ALIGN=RIGHT VALIGN=TOP><TD>
Grant D. Savage
<P>&nbsp;</TD></TR>
<A NAME=POEM3></A>
<TR ALIGN=LEFT VALIGN=TOP><TD><P><FONT SIZE=+1>sun-bright morning
<br>
dragons of factory smoke
<br>
dissolved by wind
</FONT></TD></TR> <TR ALIGN=RIGHT VALIGN=TOP><TD>
Christopher Herold
<P>&nbsp;</TD></TR>
<A NAME=POEM5></A>
<TR ALIGN=LEFT VALIGN=TOP><TD><P><FONT SIZE=+1>after all the things
<br>
that have gone wrong&nbsp;&#8212;
<br>
plum blossoms
</FONT></TD></TR> <TR ALIGN=RIGHT VALIGN=TOP><TD>
Sanjukta Asopa
<P>&nbsp;</TD></TR>
<A NAME=POEM7></A>
<TR ALIGN=LEFT VALIGN=TOP><TD><P><FONT SIZE=+1>I find myself
<br>
losing the trail . . .
<br>
greening woods
</FONT></TD></TR> <TR ALIGN=RIGHT VALIGN=TOP><TD>
Kirsty Karkow
<P>&nbsp;</TD></TR>
<A NAME=POEM9></A>
<TR ALIGN=LEFT VALIGN=TOP><TD><P><FONT SIZE=+1>spring cleaning&nbsp;&#8212;
<br>
my daughter finds the key
<br>
to the music box
</FONT></TD></TR> <TR ALIGN=RIGHT VALIGN=TOP><TD>
Ola Lindberg
<P>&nbsp;</TD></TR>
